        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>Divinatory text predicting different events, mostly of unfortunate character, that will happen or not depending on the day of the 
                    week on which the feast day of St John the Baptist falls, similar to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6702MashafaKobor">Maṣḥafa kobor</ref>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5048Hassabat#Kobor">No item: LIT5048Hassabat, could not check for Kobor</ref> (in the form <foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ፡ ኮቦር፡</foreign>, and texts in 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CamOr1883">CUL Or. 1883, f. 37v</ref> (cf. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/H82JZAFC"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Ullendorff1961Catalogue"/><title level="m">Catalogue of Ethiopian manuscripts in the Cambridge University Library</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Edward</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ullendorff</t:surname></author><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stephen</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Wright</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Cambridge</pubPlace><publisher>Cambridge University Press</publisher><date>1961</date><citedRange unit="item">LVIII</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">58-59</citedRange></bibl>),
                    Éthiopien 590 (Griaule 282) = Strelcyn 590, f. 34v (cf. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/M97KF3UK"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1954Griaule"/><title level="m">Catalogue des manuscrits éthiopiens (Collection Griaule)&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, IV:&lt;/hi&gt; Éthiopien 373 (Griaule 69) - Éthiopien 674 (Gruiauel 366) Nouvelles acquiistions: Éthiopien 301–304, 675–687</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stefan</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Strelcyn</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Paris</pubPlace><publisher>Imprimerie nationale</publisher><date>1954</date><citedRange unit="item">590,2</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">174-175</citedRange></bibl>, indicated as "Asāba
                    kobar, en amarique") as well as
                    Wellcome XVII, from f. 62r to 62v  (cf. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/H8WBU22B"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1972Wellcome"/><title level="a">Catalogue of Ethiopian Manuscripts of the Wellcome Institute of the History of Medicine in London</title><title level="j">Bulletin of the School of Oriental and African Studies, University of London</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stefan</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Strelcyn</t:surname></author><date>1972</date><biblScope unit="volume">35</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">27-55</biblScope><note type="url">http://www.jstor.org/stable/612793</note><citedRange unit="item">XVII, 35</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">39-42</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
